@Florian i built a simple example demonstrating what i believe is a blocking nature of the top level await, notice how long it takes to render the UI depending on if you import snarkyjs (using both import styles). If you skip snarkyjs, the UI renders like 2s faster in this case

https://stackblitz.com/edit/nextjs-1vr6wo?file=pages%2Findex.js,.babelrc

```
console.time('import snarkyjs');
// this import can't be timed, but appears to be equally as slow as the `await import`
import { Field } from 'snarkyjs';
// const { Field } = await import('snarkyjs');
console.timeEnd('import snarkyjs');

console.log('Field', Field(0).toString());
```

In my opinion it blocks the render if its imported at the top level, you can see it for yourself in the playground i linked
